title: Philippines Exports YoY
description: Exports YoY in Philippines increased to 7 percent in September from -2 percent in August of 2022. Exports YoY in Philippines averaged 10.20 percent from 1958 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 155.30 percent in June of 1973 and a record low of -41.30 percent in April of 2020. Exports in Philippines account for nearly a third of GDP. Major exports are: electronic products (42 percent), other manufactures (10 percent) and woodcrafts and furniture (6 percent). Philippines is also the worldâ€™s largest producer of coconut, pineapple and abaca. Philippines's main export partners are: Japan (21 percent), the United States (15 percent), China (12 percent) and Hong Kong (8 percent). This page includes a chart with historical data for Philippines Exports YoY.
author: Philippine Statistics Authority
